                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/682: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-05T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 5, 1938—noon.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. German military advisers left for Hong Kong at 9:00 this morning on special
                    train provided by the Chinese Government.</p>
                <p>It is understood that on July 2 a banquet was given in their honor by the
                    Generalissimo and on July 4 by the Minister of War. The press reports today that
                    the Chinese Government, appreciating the difficult position in which the
                    advisers were placed, had voluntarily released them from their unexpired
                    contracts.</p>
                <p>A Chinese Government spokesman is quoted in the press today as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The German advisers are leaving with our assurance of high appreciation
                            of their past service and also with our very best wishes.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
